The paper deals with mechanism design for two-sided markets, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The use of combinatorial auctions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of valuation functions, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with budget balance and incentive compatibility, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT).
